                    <div class="question">Why oh why another CSS framework?!</div>
                    <div class="answer">lol</div>
                    <div class="answer">I know...</div>
                    <div class="answer">The thing is that after years of developing, client's needs were often so custom that using Bootstrap or Foundation eventually required tons of styles to override the ones provided by the framework, sometimes even having to fight against predefined <code>!importants</code> (headbang)...</div>
                    <div class="answer">So I went over all my work over the previous years in front end and recompiled and updated a set of styles which became Basecoat, a framework that aims to be as simple, yet as beautiful as possible, and that empowers you to build on top of it :)</div>

